entry.summary:
The VS Code 1.70 release notes include a nifty new experimental editor feature ‚Äì sticky function signatures!
Add the following to your settings.json:
{
  "editor.experimental.stickyScroll.enabled": true
}

One might argue that it's an unnecessary feature because if you're writing clean code, you won't need it, but still... I'm there for pretty editor UI features!
Scrolling in VS Code showing that function signatures stick at the top.


After sharing this feature on Twitter, Elio Struyf pointed out that you can also configure the sticky element's background color. üéâ
{
  "workbench.colorCustomizations": {
    "editorStickyScroll.background": "#D44",
    "editorStickyScrollHover.background": "#A00"
  }
}

It might need a little tweaking to make it work with your color theme, though. üôà
VS Code with colored sticky function signatures.






